The writer of this work was D-Avrn Hom: of Gonscaor‘r, the well known author of the History of the House and Race of Douglas and Augus, He was the second son of Sir David, the seventh of the Barons of Wedderburn, whose deeds are recorded in these pages, and much of what is known of his early life will be found interspersed in the account which he gives of his bro- ther, the eighth baron. He was born, it is usually supposed, about the year 1560.'
